<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 314.</seg></opener>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to
                            Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-01-07"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 7,
                            1885</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 1058.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your dispatch No. 917, of
                        the 22d ultimo, in relation to Mormon recruits from India, I have to inform
                        you that Lord Granville’s suggestion as to instructing the American consuls
                        in India to co-operate with the British authorities there has been adopted
                        by this Department and that suitable instructions have been given to the
                        consul-general at Calcutta, and to our consuls at Bombay and Singapore, on
                        the subject.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>